WEBVTT

00:05.965 --> 00:07.967
♪ ♪

00:14.014 --> 00:15.599
[Belly] The Fourth of July
in Cousins

00:15.599 --> 00:17.184
is all about traditions.

00:17.184 --> 00:19.228
Susannah decks out
the whole house,

00:19.228 --> 00:21.021
the dads come up
for the weekend,

00:21.021 --> 00:24.400
the boys steam clams
and shoot off fireworks.

00:24.400 --> 00:27.862
All the other Fourth of Julys,
I was just tagging along.

00:27.862 --> 00:30.072
But this year, I have friends.

00:30.072 --> 00:31.574
I have plans.

00:31.574 --> 00:33.075
[Jeremiah] Can I finish
your milk?

00:33.075 --> 00:34.577
- Here.
- Mm.

00:34.577 --> 00:37.371
- [laughs]
- [slurps]

00:37.371 --> 00:39.123
[Conrad] Yo, I'm gonna go
wash the clams.

00:39.123 --> 00:40.750
- Did you get the lighter fluid?
- Mm.

00:40.750 --> 00:43.002
- Yeah, it's already
on the beach.
- [whistles]

00:43.002 --> 00:44.211
Mm.

00:44.211 --> 00:45.421
Are we done
with the portrait yet?

00:45.421 --> 00:46.881
Yeah, for today.

00:46.881 --> 00:49.091
But you do look good
in a dress shirt, Steven.

00:49.091 --> 00:50.259
Uh, which makes me think

00:50.259 --> 00:52.303
if Belly doesn't hurry up
and ask Cam

00:52.303 --> 00:54.388
to that ball,
you should take her.

00:54.388 --> 00:56.223
Ew. No way.

00:56.223 --> 00:57.892
No, no, no, yeah, yeah, yeah.
I'm already going with Shayla.

00:57.892 --> 01:00.060
To the debutante ball?

01:00.060 --> 01:01.729
Yes.

01:01.729 --> 01:03.481
As an escort?

01:03.481 --> 01:05.149
Wrap your head around it,
Mom, all right?

01:05.149 --> 01:06.650
Shayla's coming today
with Nicole and Gigi,

01:06.650 --> 01:07.651
so you'll meet her.

01:07.651 --> 01:10.196
That's wonderful.

01:10.196 --> 01:11.947
Oh, and don't forget,
Ms. Covington's first dance

01:11.947 --> 01:14.074
rehearsal is tomorrow,
so, uh, tick-tock.

01:14.074 --> 01:16.410
I'm asking Cam today.

01:16.410 --> 01:19.079
I don't know my kids anymore.

01:19.079 --> 01:20.998
Wait, are you wearing makeup?

01:20.998 --> 01:23.501
- Yeah, she's wearing makeup.
- Oh, my... She definitely is.

01:23.501 --> 01:24.919
- Ooh!
- Mom!

01:24.919 --> 01:27.755
- So what? We're having a party.
- Mm-hmm.

01:27.755 --> 01:29.882
I'm sure it has nothing
to do with John

01:29.882 --> 01:31.634
- coming to the clam bake?
- Oh, please.

01:31.634 --> 01:33.052
The husbands always come
for the Fourth.

01:33.052 --> 01:35.179
He's not your husband anymore.

01:35.179 --> 01:37.056
Oops. Yeah. [chuckles]
Ex-husband.

01:37.056 --> 01:38.349
You know,
I still don't understand

01:38.349 --> 01:39.642
why you invited
Dad's girlfriend.

01:39.642 --> 01:41.560
Her name is Victoria,

01:41.560 --> 01:43.270
and your father wanted
us all to meet her.

01:43.270 --> 01:45.856
Oh, Belly, I need you
to make up the guest bed.

01:45.856 --> 01:47.817
Wait, Dad and Victoria
are staying here?

01:48.943 --> 01:50.778
In the room next to mine?

01:50.778 --> 01:52.780
Yeah.

01:52.780 --> 01:54.323
- [groans]
- [chuckles]

01:54.323 --> 01:56.158
Oh, speaking of dads,
yours called.

01:56.158 --> 01:57.868
He's closing a deal, so

01:57.868 --> 02:00.079
- he can't come.
- What?

02:00.079 --> 02:01.372
[door closes]

02:01.372 --> 02:03.582
- Did you say Dad's not coming?
- Mm-hmm.

02:03.582 --> 02:06.210
But I got some serious fireworks
for the show this year.

02:06.210 --> 02:08.379
We'll take a video.

02:08.379 --> 02:09.922
It's not the same.

02:09.922 --> 02:11.632
[Susannah] I know.

02:16.345 --> 02:17.638
What're you smiling
over there for?

02:19.431 --> 02:21.058
No reason.

02:26.188 --> 02:28.899
[Susannah] Laurel, will you
come help me move the table?

02:28.899 --> 02:30.568
Be right there.

02:45.249 --> 02:48.335
You got to fold the bottom sheet
at a 45 degree angle

02:48.335 --> 02:50.045
if you want tight corners.

02:52.256 --> 02:54.425
- Yeah, not like that.
- [Belly laughing]

02:54.425 --> 02:57.136
Then help me.

03:00.389 --> 03:03.058
- You got to pull this down.
- Okay.

03:03.058 --> 03:05.394
[clears throat]
Like this. Come here.

03:06.896 --> 03:09.648
[Belly] Is this
what it would be like?

03:09.648 --> 03:11.942
If we were older?

03:11.942 --> 03:15.112
- Me and Conrad together?
- See?

03:15.112 --> 03:16.739
[♪ Caroline Polachek: "So Hot
You're Hurting My Feelings"]

03:16.739 --> 03:18.157
Thank you. [chuckles]

03:19.783 --> 03:21.785
[sighs] Don't you think
it's weird that my dad

03:21.785 --> 03:23.245
is staying here with Victoria?

03:23.245 --> 03:26.290
Well, I'm sure they're
not gonna have loud sex.

03:26.290 --> 03:29.209
[scoffs] That's foul.

03:29.209 --> 03:30.419
Ugh.

03:30.419 --> 03:31.962
And why is my mom
letting him bring

03:31.962 --> 03:34.340
- his bitchy girlfriend anyway?
- Hey.

03:34.340 --> 03:36.675
How do you know she's bitchy?
What if she's, like...

03:36.675 --> 03:38.302
a really nice person
or something? [laughs]

03:38.302 --> 03:39.720
[laughs]

03:39.720 --> 03:42.806
Uh, what if-- uh, and-and,
like, just hear me out--

03:42.806 --> 03:44.850
- she's a bitch.
- [both laughing]

03:44.892 --> 03:46.352
[laughing] Stop.

03:46.352 --> 03:48.562
It's gonna to be fine, okay?
Don't worry about it.

03:48.562 --> 03:50.481
[car horn honks]

03:50.481 --> 03:51.815
I'm sorry your dad's not coming.

03:51.815 --> 03:53.484
Don't be. I'm not.

03:53.484 --> 03:55.277
[Laurel] Belly.

03:57.029 --> 03:58.781
[whispers] The bitch is here.

03:58.781 --> 04:00.324
♪ It's hurting my feelings ♪

04:00.324 --> 04:04.495
♪ I get a little lonely ♪

04:04.495 --> 04:08.707
♪ Get a little more close
to me ♪

04:08.707 --> 04:13.087
♪ You're the only one
who knows me, babe ♪

04:13.087 --> 04:15.923
♪ So hot, you're hurting
my feelings...

04:15.923 --> 04:18.676
I was kind of hoping for
a vapid ditz in Lululemons.

04:18.676 --> 04:21.345
- Stereotypical midlife crisis?
- Yeah, that.

04:23.305 --> 04:24.932
- You have a much better ass.
- [slaps butt]

04:24.932 --> 04:26.558
- [chuckles]
- You made it.

04:26.558 --> 04:28.852
- Yes.
- [Laurel] How was the trip?

04:28.852 --> 04:30.854
I forgot how crazy it gets here
around the Fourth.

04:30.854 --> 04:32.690
We almost hit a guy in a Segway

04:32.690 --> 04:34.108
with, uh, red, white,
and blue body paint.

04:34.108 --> 04:35.985
[chuckles]

04:35.985 --> 04:38.237
- Oh, this is, uh...
- Victoria. Hi.

04:38.237 --> 04:41.407
Thank you so much for having me.
I'm such a big fan of your work.

04:41.407 --> 04:42.408
[Laurel] Thanks. [chuckles]

04:44.243 --> 04:45.452
She's hot.

04:45.452 --> 04:46.870
- [Steven] Dude.
- [Jeremiah] What?

04:46.870 --> 04:48.831
I'm just saying what
everyone else is thinking.

04:48.831 --> 04:51.041
I wasn't thinking that.

04:51.041 --> 04:53.794
Yo, that could be
their future stepmom.

04:53.794 --> 04:56.046
- [Steven] Dude, what the hell?
- Don't push me.

04:56.046 --> 04:58.132
Guys, they're coming,
they're coming. Ah!

04:58.132 --> 05:00.718
Go, go, go, go, go.

05:00.718 --> 05:02.011
- [Steven] Hey.
- [Belly chuckles]

05:02.011 --> 05:03.595
[whispers] Be nice.

05:03.595 --> 05:05.889
Hey.

05:05.889 --> 05:07.516
Come give your old man
a hug, huh?

05:07.516 --> 05:08.642
- Dad!
- Hey, Dad.

05:08.642 --> 05:11.937
Oh, my gosh! Um...

05:11.937 --> 05:13.731
This is Victoria.

05:13.731 --> 05:16.066
Hi, guys. It's-it's
really great to meet you.

05:16.066 --> 05:18.694
I've heard nothing
but five-star reviews.

05:20.696 --> 05:22.906
- Here, let's put this
in the kitchen.
- Okay.

05:25.159 --> 05:26.702
There is no way she's 27.

05:26.702 --> 05:28.037
We have to grab
her wallet and check

05:28.037 --> 05:30.789
- her ID.
- She's in grad school. Chill.

05:30.789 --> 05:33.042
I can't chill. I mean,
knock-off Dakota Johnson

05:33.042 --> 05:35.002
- has her claws in our dad.
- Yeah.

05:37.212 --> 05:38.881
Oh, my goodness.
This is the most

05:38.881 --> 05:40.257
beautiful kitchen
that I've ever seen.

05:40.257 --> 05:42.009
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

05:42.009 --> 05:43.343
Steven, can you get
your dad's bags

05:43.343 --> 05:44.845
and put them upstairs, please?

05:44.845 --> 05:46.555
Yeah, I-I just need your keys
to pop the trunk, then.

05:46.555 --> 05:49.475
Actually, Vick and I decided
to stay in town this weekend.

05:49.475 --> 05:50.934
Figured you guys
had a packed house.

05:50.934 --> 05:52.728
- Oh, that sounds fun.
- Oh, yeah.

05:52.728 --> 05:54.855
- Well, are you sure?
- Whatever you think is best.

05:54.855 --> 05:57.483
So... I convinced John

05:57.483 --> 05:59.359
to stop at a fruit stand
on the way over,

05:59.359 --> 06:01.028
and I figured I could
make some pomegranate

06:01.028 --> 06:03.489
- margaritas later.
- Oh, how thoughtful of you.

06:03.489 --> 06:04.490
[doorbell rings]

06:04.490 --> 06:06.408
Oh, I'll get it.

06:06.408 --> 06:08.994
I... Shayla...

06:08.994 --> 06:10.412
here.

06:10.412 --> 06:13.332
The debs have arrived.

06:13.332 --> 06:14.833
- [♪ Francis On My Mind:
"Swimming Pools"]
- ♪ Every day is summer ♪

06:14.833 --> 06:16.085
♪ Summer ♪

06:16.085 --> 06:17.669
♪ We're still burning up ♪

06:17.669 --> 06:19.254
♪ When the sun goes down ♪

06:19.254 --> 06:21.423
♪ Oh, you make me ♪

06:21.423 --> 06:24.510
♪ Wonder, wonder ♪

06:24.510 --> 06:26.178
♪ How I'm gonna live
when you're not...

06:26.178 --> 06:27.596
And then we do
Hayley Kiyoko next.

06:27.596 --> 06:29.098
She's super vibey.
You would love her.

06:29.098 --> 06:30.724
Love. Do you listen to SZA?

06:30.724 --> 06:33.102
I'm kind of offended you felt
the need to ask me that.

06:33.102 --> 06:35.312
Okay. Of course.
What else do you have on there?

06:35.312 --> 06:37.231
I can't stop smelling you.

06:37.231 --> 06:39.441
- Okay, well, it's Le Labo.
- Mmm.

06:39.441 --> 06:40.859
Well, I "le lab" it.

06:40.859 --> 06:43.112
- [both laugh]
- You "le lab" it?

06:43.112 --> 06:45.489
- [both laugh]
- That's what
my family does, too.

06:45.489 --> 06:47.449
- Oh, really? Do you know
what you're gonna be?
- Oh, yeah?

06:47.449 --> 06:48.784
My dad runs a hedge fund.
I'm not really sure

06:48.784 --> 06:50.285
what he does
much more than that,

06:50.285 --> 06:52.204
but, growing up, I always
thought he worked on bushes.

06:52.204 --> 06:54.540
I still think that. [laughs]

06:54.540 --> 06:55.791
And what does your mom do?

06:55.791 --> 06:58.001
Mom. Come on,
stop interrogating her.

06:58.001 --> 07:00.129
[Shayla] It's all right.
She's at a wellness retreat

07:00.129 --> 07:01.588
in Arizona until August.
Code for

07:01.588 --> 07:03.298
"I need to get away
from my family for a bit."

07:03.298 --> 07:06.468
[Gigi] Shayla. You have to read
this text. Come here.

07:06.468 --> 07:07.719
Duty calls,

07:07.719 --> 07:10.055
but it was so nice to meet
the both of you.

07:10.055 --> 07:11.890
You have really raised
an incredible son.

07:11.890 --> 07:13.267
He's extremely respectful.

07:13.267 --> 07:14.893
- [Laurel] Thank you.
- See you later.

07:14.893 --> 07:17.521
♪ Can't stay in
the shallow, shallow...

07:17.521 --> 07:18.981
What a rad girl, Steven.

07:18.981 --> 07:20.649
[Steven] Ugh,
don't say "rad," Dad.

07:20.649 --> 07:22.401
- D-Don't... No, don't say that.
- No, I'm a rad dad.

07:22.401 --> 07:25.445
I like her. She's confident,
knows who she is.

07:25.445 --> 07:27.364
I'm surprised a girl like that
would want to deb.

07:27.364 --> 07:28.866
♪ And I'm never coming out...

07:28.866 --> 07:30.159
[John] Is there a place
around here I can rent a tux

07:30.159 --> 07:31.451
for you?

07:31.451 --> 07:33.370
- Um...
- [Shalya] Steven, come here.

07:33.370 --> 07:35.539
No. No, no, no.
I-I've got it covered, Dad.

07:35.539 --> 07:36.748
Thank you.

07:36.748 --> 07:37.916
Yeah.

07:37.916 --> 07:40.502
So, tell me about this deb ball.

07:40.502 --> 07:43.922
Yeah, so, um, apparently,
it's for girls like me.

07:43.922 --> 07:46.633
Girls who, uh,
don't know who they are.

07:46.633 --> 07:48.468
Belly, I didn't mean it
like that.

07:48.468 --> 07:50.262
[Victoria] You know,
actually, my cousin did it

07:50.262 --> 07:52.764
in Chicago and they raised a ton
of money for public schools.

07:52.764 --> 07:54.641
Great.

07:54.641 --> 07:56.768
Yeah. Uh, Belly,

07:56.768 --> 07:58.770
would you mind showing me
where I can find a bathroom?

08:00.355 --> 08:01.773
Sure.

08:01.773 --> 08:05.194
♪ So I'm diving
right into you...

08:05.194 --> 08:07.905
[John] Victoria really did
read your book, you know?

08:07.905 --> 08:09.781
I'm surprised she didn't run
screaming by the end of it.

08:09.781 --> 08:12.367
I'm a novelist, John.
I write fiction.

08:12.367 --> 08:13.577
Tell that to Victoria.

08:13.577 --> 08:15.078
But how late can she stay?

08:15.078 --> 08:16.705
Wouldn't want her parents
getting upset.

08:16.705 --> 08:17.873
- Okay.
- She can drink, right?

08:17.873 --> 08:19.249
I'd hate for those pomegranates

08:19.249 --> 08:20.292
- to go to waste.
- Okay.

08:20.292 --> 08:21.835
- No, I understand.
- [laughs]

08:24.338 --> 08:26.006
God, I missed this.

08:26.006 --> 08:28.467
All of us together again
for a good old Fisher Fourth.

08:28.467 --> 08:30.344
[exhales] Almost everyone.

08:32.346 --> 08:33.722
So Adam couldn't make it, huh?

08:35.182 --> 08:37.309
Apparently not.

08:41.939 --> 08:43.482
- That's dope.
- [laughs softly]

08:43.482 --> 08:45.108
How'd you learn to make these?

08:45.108 --> 08:48.195
So I actually spent
a summer in this desert town

08:48.195 --> 08:51.531
in Texas near the border
called Marfa.

08:51.531 --> 08:53.283
And there was a bar there
that served these,

08:53.283 --> 08:55.118
and I told the bartender
that I would not leave

08:55.118 --> 08:57.663
until he showed me
exactly how he made these.

08:57.663 --> 09:00.082
[chuckles]

09:00.082 --> 09:02.000
Can I try a sip?

09:02.000 --> 09:04.253
Are your parents cool with that?

09:04.253 --> 09:06.964
- Yeah, yeah, no,
they don't care.
- Oh, then, sure.

09:08.173 --> 09:09.675
I'm gonna take this out
to your dad.

09:09.675 --> 09:11.593
Do you mind taking those out
to Susannah and your mom?

09:11.593 --> 09:13.679
- Yeah, sure.
- Thanks, love.

09:20.269 --> 09:22.771
Oh, well, how is it?
Strong? [chuckles]

09:22.771 --> 09:25.232
- [laughs] That is amazing.
Yeah.
- Is it?

09:29.486 --> 09:31.488
Mmm. No wonder you like it.

09:31.488 --> 09:34.700
- It tastes just like a Slurpee.
- Yeah, exactly.

09:34.700 --> 09:36.910
- But I have an idea.
- Oh, no.

09:36.910 --> 09:38.954
Sous-chef, I'm gonna need
some more pomegranate juice.

09:38.954 --> 09:40.372
[Jeremiah] You got it.

09:42.165 --> 09:44.751
What are you guys making?

09:44.751 --> 09:47.337
Pomegranate margaritas,
but with a twist.

09:47.337 --> 09:49.047
Well, you got to use
the good blender.

09:50.048 --> 09:52.134
Oh, I-I haven't used that thing

09:52.134 --> 09:54.594
since the great
Kool-Aid debacle of 2011.

09:54.594 --> 09:57.556
[laughs] I remember,
the counters were sticky for...

09:57.556 --> 10:00.350
- two summers?
- [laughs] Yeah. Just about.

10:00.350 --> 10:03.145
Dad kept his, uh,
briefcase in my room for a year.

10:03.145 --> 10:07.024
"As a reminder that all mistakes
are not reversible."

10:07.024 --> 10:10.902
Wait, won't he be mad
if he finds out?

10:10.902 --> 10:13.155
Well, he's not gonna find out.
He's not coming.

10:14.865 --> 10:16.742
- [laughs] Okay.
- Yeah.

10:16.742 --> 10:18.285
Yeah.

10:18.285 --> 10:19.995
[Conrad] Thank you, sir.

10:19.995 --> 10:22.122
Oh, she's going
for the good stuff.

10:22.122 --> 10:23.749
Yeah...

10:23.749 --> 10:25.167
We don't need another debacle.

10:25.167 --> 10:26.668
- Yeah.
- Stop it, stop.

10:26.668 --> 10:27.711
- No, stop.
- A lot more,
a lot more tequila.

10:27.711 --> 10:29.254
No, no, no, no, no!

10:29.254 --> 10:31.381
[chuckles]

10:33.675 --> 10:35.385
No, keep your hands on it.

10:35.385 --> 10:37.596
Keep your hands on it.
[chuckles]

10:38.638 --> 10:39.890
Man, you know what I miss?

10:39.890 --> 10:41.516
Huh?

10:41.516 --> 10:43.143
Watching Laurel
put Dad in his place.

10:43.143 --> 10:45.395
You know, she'd walk in,
she'd be like, "Adam."

10:45.395 --> 10:47.689
[Laurel] Adam.

10:47.689 --> 10:49.066
You came.

10:49.066 --> 10:50.650
- Happy Fourth.
- [Jeremiah] Dad!

10:50.650 --> 10:52.903
- [laughs] You came.
- Hey.

10:52.903 --> 10:54.821
Hey, guys. Hey, Connie.

10:54.821 --> 10:57.366
I'll have a little of what
you're mixing up there.

10:57.366 --> 10:58.742
- Ooh.
- Yeah, sure.

10:58.742 --> 11:00.744
- Hey, thanks, Belly.
- Oh, you're gonna love

11:00.744 --> 11:02.579
the firework show this year.
It's gonna be the best one yet.

11:02.579 --> 11:04.873
I believe it. [chuckles]

11:04.873 --> 11:06.541
[Susannah] Where'd everyone go?

11:06.541 --> 11:09.086
[Adam] Hey.

11:09.086 --> 11:10.087
Adam.

11:12.089 --> 11:13.840
You managed to get off work.

11:13.840 --> 11:16.551
Yeah, couldn't miss
the Fourth with my family.

11:16.551 --> 11:18.595
[chuckles]

11:23.725 --> 11:26.311
All right, well,
let's get back to the party.

11:26.311 --> 11:29.314
Okay, let's go, kids.

11:29.314 --> 11:31.233
All right.

11:33.151 --> 11:34.903
Hey, Connie, can I talk
to you for a minute?

11:34.903 --> 11:36.113
[Conrad] I'm gonna
head to the beach.

11:38.323 --> 11:40.784
How you feeling, Suz?

11:40.784 --> 11:42.953
Listen, a friend of mine
at Sloan Kettering

11:42.953 --> 11:45.288
said they're starting an
experimental trial soon after...

11:45.288 --> 11:47.499
What are you doing here, Adam?

11:48.542 --> 11:50.127
Laurel called me this morning,

11:50.127 --> 11:51.628
said, "Get your ass here,"
so I'm here.

11:51.628 --> 11:53.588
She shouldn't have done that.

11:55.257 --> 11:56.425
You didn't know.

11:56.425 --> 11:58.927
No, I didn't.

11:58.927 --> 12:00.554
Well, I thought
you'd changed your mind.

12:02.597 --> 12:06.601
Well, since it's done, we, um,
we just need to get through it.

12:06.601 --> 12:09.438
Jere's really excited
to show you his fireworks.

12:09.438 --> 12:12.149
I'm not ruining the Fourth
for the boys.

12:14.734 --> 12:16.653
[door opens]

12:16.653 --> 12:18.905
- Hot pink?
- Oh...

12:18.905 --> 12:20.115
Or if...

12:20.115 --> 12:22.033
May I present

12:22.033 --> 12:24.453
- The Belly Special?
- [whooping]

12:24.453 --> 12:26.371
- Ooh, very nice.
- Those look awesome.

12:26.371 --> 12:27.789
- [chuckles]
