we were young...

13:22.385 --> 13:24.596
- [Gigi] Jeremiah, drink.
- [Jeremiah] No!

13:24.596 --> 13:26.598
- Shayla. Drink up.
- What?

13:26.598 --> 13:28.934
Chug that.

13:28.934 --> 13:31.269
Oh, hey. Gigi, drink.

13:31.269 --> 13:32.896
- [whoops]
- [Shayla] She was
going in there.

13:32.896 --> 13:34.689
♪ Snakes and ladders ♪

13:34.689 --> 13:36.149
♪ Climbing up for days ♪

13:36.149 --> 13:38.068
♪ We're invincible, we said...

13:38.068 --> 13:39.569
Drink.

13:39.569 --> 13:41.404
[Steven] Oh, drink!

13:41.404 --> 13:42.531
[Shayla] What?

13:42.531 --> 13:43.615
- [indistinct chatter]
- Oh, my God,

13:43.615 --> 13:44.658
why am I so bad at this?

13:44.658 --> 13:46.034
Ah!

13:46.034 --> 13:48.286
Yay! Here you go.

13:48.286 --> 13:50.330
Wait, wait, wait.
That's a new...

13:50.330 --> 13:51.998
- Oh...
- [whooping]

13:51.998 --> 13:54.042
- Yes.
- Oh...

13:54.042 --> 13:55.502
[laughter]

13:55.502 --> 13:56.920
- Come on.
- [chuckles]

13:57.963 --> 13:59.089
No way... Oh!

13:59.089 --> 14:00.507
[Cam] That's a shame.

14:00.507 --> 14:02.884
Next time... Oh!

14:02.884 --> 14:06.471
[laughter]

14:06.471 --> 14:08.848
- We killed it. Isn't it...
- We killed it.

14:08.848 --> 14:10.308
- You did.
- Come on.

14:11.393 --> 14:14.980
♪ Thinking about everybody...

14:14.980 --> 14:16.273
[Cam] Oh, let's go.

14:16.273 --> 14:18.149
- That's my boy.
- That's one.

14:18.149 --> 14:20.193
- That's pretty good.
That's pretty good.
- [Cam] What was that?

14:20.193 --> 14:21.570
- Maybe next time.
- Come on, Steven.

14:23.780 --> 14:25.574
Let's go! Oh, my God!

14:25.574 --> 14:27.492
[both laugh]

14:27.492 --> 14:29.244
- [Steven] Oh, yeah!
- What happened?

14:29.244 --> 14:32.664
[fades] Oh, yeah! Oh, yeah!

14:32.664 --> 14:37.043
♪ 'Cause if they haven't
caught you yet...

14:37.043 --> 14:40.046
- You are so good at games.
- Yeah, I know you're kidding.

14:40.046 --> 14:42.048
[indistinct chatter]

14:49.180 --> 14:51.474
[Gigi] Oh, okay, but did
you know that she was one

14:51.474 --> 14:53.727
of the last people to visit
Lindsay Lohan's beach club

14:53.727 --> 14:54.978
in Mykonos before it closed?

14:54.978 --> 14:56.438
- Are you serious?
- Mm-hmm.

14:56.438 --> 14:57.856
Oh, my God, I'd die for Lindsay.

14:57.856 --> 14:59.274
Ugh, she's a queen.

14:59.274 --> 15:01.443
[Nicole] Ibiza
is superior, though.

15:01.443 --> 15:02.652
[Shayla] As if.

15:02.652 --> 15:04.321
- [Nicole] You don't agree?
- No.

15:04.321 --> 15:06.781
- Back me up.
- [Jeremiah] Hey, Connie, catch.

15:06.781 --> 15:09.242
- Yes, no, I... Yes, I agree.
- He's lost.

15:09.242 --> 15:11.494
"Yes, no, yes, no, I agree."

15:11.494 --> 15:13.413
- [Shayla] Shut up.
- Doesn't know what
he's talking about.

15:13.413 --> 15:16.207
[Shayla] He knows what he's
talking about. He's on my side.

15:16.207 --> 15:17.459
[voices fading]

15:17.459 --> 15:19.169
♪ ♪

15:27.010 --> 15:28.845
- [♪ Vampire Weekend:
"This Life"]
- ♪ Baby, I know love ♪

15:28.845 --> 15:31.723
♪ Isn't what I thought it was ♪

15:31.723 --> 15:37.437
♪ 'Cause I've never known
a love like this before ya...

15:37.437 --> 15:39.147
[sighs]

15:39.147 --> 15:41.024
- Here, let me help.
- [indistinct chatter]

15:41.024 --> 15:43.943
- What is wrong with...
- I don't need it.

15:43.943 --> 15:45.987
♪ Baby, I know dreams ♪

15:45.987 --> 15:49.157
♪ Tend to crumble at extremes...

15:49.157 --> 15:51.368
All right, here it comes.

15:51.368 --> 15:54.371
Oh, easy with the velocity,
Tom Brady.

15:55.413 --> 15:57.248
Ho, hoo.

15:57.248 --> 15:58.375
Interception. [chuckles]

16:00.377 --> 16:01.795
Go deep.

16:01.795 --> 16:03.213
Your spiral's looking
pretty tight.

16:03.213 --> 16:05.465
- Must be in the genes.
- Touchdown, Patriots.

16:05.465 --> 16:08.343
Oh, hey. I talked
to Coach Walsh from Brown.

16:08.343 --> 16:10.929
He says there's a spot on
summer sessions waiting for you.

16:10.929 --> 16:13.598
- I'm good here.
- [Jeremiah] Hey, Dad.

16:13.598 --> 16:15.850
Uh, we're lighting that big
firework you got in Mexico,

16:15.850 --> 16:18.645
the one that, uh,
makes the big palm tree.

16:18.645 --> 16:20.980
- It's gonna be awesome.
- Can't wait.

16:20.980 --> 16:22.440
Just don't aim it near
the house, all right?

16:22.440 --> 16:24.067
Hey, come here, I want
to show you how to run a post.

16:24.067 --> 16:25.819
Yeah, we got to go
dig the clam pit.

16:25.819 --> 16:27.404
Oh. I'll come help.

16:27.404 --> 16:29.364
Why don't you go spend
some time with Mom?

16:35.161 --> 16:36.830
[Nicole] I don't get Conrad.

16:36.830 --> 16:39.791
It's, like, one minute
he's all over me,

16:39.791 --> 16:42.669
and he stays over, but then
we don't even fuck, right?

16:42.669 --> 16:45.130
And then this morning,
he's, like, super into me,

16:45.130 --> 16:48.717
he's all over me, and now
he's like, "Oh, football."

16:48.717 --> 16:52.846
Yeah, no, he's really
hard to read sometimes.

16:52.846 --> 16:55.682
- [laughs] Like all the time.
- Yeah.

16:55.682 --> 16:58.393
Do you really think he likes me?

16:59.978 --> 17:02.147
Yeah. Yeah, totally.

17:02.147 --> 17:05.900
I mean, he talks
about you a lot.

17:05.900 --> 17:08.403
- Really?
- Yeah. Mm-hmm.

17:08.403 --> 17:09.654
[Cam] Hi.

17:09.654 --> 17:12.574
You may want to hydrate. Water.

17:12.574 --> 17:15.326
Cam Cameron, you are so sweet.
Isn't he sweet?

17:15.326 --> 17:16.745
- [Cam chuckles]
- Mm-hmm.

17:16.745 --> 17:18.329
- [giggles]
- Uh, do you want to go

17:18.329 --> 17:19.581
for a walk on the beach?

17:19.581 --> 17:21.833
Belly, by the way,
I love that dress.

17:21.833 --> 17:25.462
Really? Thanks, I...
Taylor got it for me, actually.

17:25.462 --> 17:27.088
Mm, Taylor has great taste.

17:27.088 --> 17:28.465
[Belly] Yeah, I know, right?

17:28.465 --> 17:30.175
She totally does. Oh, my God.

17:30.175 --> 17:32.093
You know what?

17:32.093 --> 17:34.262
You and Taylor are, like, twins.

17:34.262 --> 17:36.598
Because you're both
mega-fashiony.

17:36.598 --> 17:38.725
- It's true. It's true.
- And you're both, like...

17:38.725 --> 17:41.519
- baddies, wouldn't you...
Baddies.
- [laughter]

17:41.519 --> 17:44.189
And you both like the same
summer boys, which is...

17:44.189 --> 17:45.774
- [chuckles] We do?
- [Cam] Come on.

17:45.774 --> 17:46.983
- Let's go for that walk.
- [Belly] No, no, no, Cam.

17:46.983 --> 17:49.360
- Yeah.
- I'm talking. One sec.

17:49.360 --> 17:53.490
Look, Shayla, like, don't worry,
because my brother is an idiot.

17:53.490 --> 17:55.784
And it didn't mean anything.
It didn't mean anything.

17:55.784 --> 17:57.619
- [Cam] Let's go for that walk.
- Wait, what didn't
mean anything?

17:57.619 --> 17:59.704
Uh, them-them kissing.

17:59.704 --> 18:01.998
- [Cam] Hey...
- It was like...
He-he, like, loves you.

18:01.998 --> 18:03.833
He loves you. And... Wait,
does anyone want another drink?

18:03.833 --> 18:05.710
I want another drink.

18:09.339 --> 18:11.007
[Jeremiah] Hey.

18:11.007 --> 18:12.717
Can you be nice to Dad
for one day?

18:12.717 --> 18:15.094
Seriously, he's trying.

18:15.094 --> 18:16.888
Good for him.

18:18.223 --> 18:21.226
Whatever you have with Dad,
squash it, all right?

18:21.226 --> 18:22.435
Please.

18:24.813 --> 18:26.815
[exhales]

18:30.109 --> 18:32.654
Yeah, it's mostly a work summer.

18:32.654 --> 18:35.490
I mean,
Princeton is pretty expensive.

18:35.490 --> 18:38.368
And t-that's if I get in, so...

18:38.368 --> 18:42.288
You will.
You got hustle like I did.

18:42.288 --> 18:44.332
Hey, have you found
the card room?

18:44.332 --> 18:45.792
At the club.

18:45.792 --> 18:47.544
It's off the men's locker room.

18:47.544 --> 18:50.588
Most days, there's a high-stakes
poker game in there.

18:50.588 --> 18:52.924
Private bar, dedicated server.

18:52.924 --> 18:54.217
And big tips?

18:54.217 --> 18:56.761
When the game's rolling,
we hand out Benjamins.

18:56.761 --> 18:58.179
[laughs]

19:00.974 --> 19:03.476
I'll put in a call,
see what I can do.

19:03.476 --> 19:05.311
Thank you.

19:09.858 --> 19:11.651
- You should. They're really...
- [Cam] Yeah?

19:11.651 --> 19:13.236
Would be cool. [chuckles]

19:13.236 --> 19:14.571
Wait, Cam, everyone's leaving.

19:14.571 --> 19:16.531
Tell them, tell them not to go.

19:16.531 --> 19:19.284
- [laughs] Tell them
not to leave.
- Stay, you guys.

19:19.284 --> 19:20.994
Uh, Shayla doesn't feel good.

19:20.994 --> 19:22.745
I think we had
a little too much.

19:22.745 --> 19:25.540
Oh... O-Okay, yeah. Well, I'm...

19:25.540 --> 19:28.501
I mean, I still feel...
I feel gr... great.

19:30.503 --> 19:32.171
You know what?

19:32.171 --> 19:34.173
Let's do this again tomorrow.

19:34.173 --> 19:36.092
- Let's do it again tomorrow.
- Okay.
- Yeah.

19:36.092 --> 19:37.093
- Bye.
- Okay.

19:37.093 --> 19:38.845
- Bye. Right?
- Belly.

19:38.845 --> 19:41.264
- Uh...
- I'm actually
gonna take off, too.

19:41.264 --> 19:43.683
- Why?
- I just think we can catch up

19:43.683 --> 19:45.476
when you're a little less...

19:45.476 --> 19:48.396
- A little less...?
- Um, just drink water.

19:48.396 --> 19:50.398
- Okay. But I'm not,
I'm not drunk.
- Drink a lot of water. Yeah.

19:50.398 --> 19:52.692
- I'm not drunk. I'm...
- Water would be good.

19:52.692 --> 19:55.111
- Call you tomorrow.
- I'm not... Okay.

20:00.366 --> 20:01.576
Hmm.

20:01.576 --> 20:04.579
[laughs] Hello, sea creature.

20:04.579 --> 20:07.206
Hello. Ooh.

20:09.375 --> 20:11.336
Hey. [chuckles]

20:11.336 --> 20:13.171
[indistinct chatter]

20:15.173 --> 20:16.382
Hey.

20:16.382 --> 20:18.927
Hey, w-whoa.
Are you guys leaving?

20:18.927 --> 20:20.386
Our Uber's here.

20:21.387 --> 20:23.556
Your Uber's here?

20:24.682 --> 20:26.309
- Just give me a minute.
- Are you sure?

20:26.309 --> 20:27.852
Yeah, it's fine.

20:31.773 --> 20:33.316
Can I come with?

20:33.316 --> 20:36.361
It's cool, we don't, like,
have to do everything together.

20:36.361 --> 20:38.363
It's not like we're a "thing."

20:38.363 --> 20:41.240
I mean, I was busy
in New York last weekend,

20:41.240 --> 20:43.493
and you were hanging out
with Taylor at Nicole's party.

20:45.536 --> 20:47.455
Taylor? No.

20:47.455 --> 20:49.958
No, no, no, no. S-She's just
Belly's best friend.

20:49.958 --> 20:51.876
I know you guys hooked up.

20:57.507 --> 20:59.425
Sh... Shayla, that doesn't...

20:59.425 --> 21:00.635
That really doesn't
mean anything.

21:00.635 --> 21:02.095
Look, she doesn't mean anything.
It's not...

21:02.095 --> 21:04.639
You can relax. I mean,
it's not like we're exclusive.

21:04.639 --> 21:07.558
Debs aren't even supposed
to date their escorts.

21:07.558 --> 21:10.520
We're just having fun, right?

21:10.520 --> 21:11.938
Nothing serious.

21:15.900 --> 21:18.069
Yeah.

21:18.069 --> 21:21.990
Yeah, no, w-we're just,
uh, having fun.

21:23.032 --> 21:24.784
Yeah.

21:24.784 --> 21:27.537
I'm glad we're on the same page.

21:27.537 --> 21:29.122
I'll, uh, I'll see you later.

21:32.583 --> 21:34.585
[engine starts]

21:39.507 --> 21:41.801
- [car door closes]
- [sighs]

21:41.801 --> 21:43.553
[Adam] Laurel, what the hell?

21:43.553 --> 21:45.555
[Laurel] Just get in here.

21:47.098 --> 21:49.642
What's going on
with you and Beck?

21:49.642 --> 21:50.935
This is all your fault.

21:50.935 --> 21:52.562
You shouldn't have
called me like that.

21:52.562 --> 21:53.980
Not without asking her.

21:53.980 --> 21:55.314
Your wife is dying of cancer

21:55.314 --> 21:57.191
and you can't make it
to her favorite holiday?

21:57.191 --> 21:59.152
I'm staying away
because she told me to.

21:59.152 --> 22:00.361
I thought you knew that.

22:01.612 --> 22:03.197
Why doesn't she want you around?

22:04.949 --> 22:07.910
- What did you do?
- I fucked up.

22:07.910 --> 22:10.747
Just like you knew I would.

22:10.747 --> 22:12.165
[door opens]

22:13.750 --> 22:15.752
[shower running]

22:18.212 --> 22:20.214
♪ ♪

22:22.842 --> 22:24.594
Oh, sea creature...

22:26.596 --> 22:28.848
Where are you?

22:28.848 --> 22:30.933
Uh, I'm in the shower.

22:30.933 --> 22:33.394
[chuckles]

22:33.394 --> 22:34.896
Everybody left.

22:34.896 --> 22:38.107
But we still got
margaritas to drink.

22:38.107 --> 22:40.943
Okay, well, I can't
drink it in the shower.

22:40.943 --> 22:42.862
Can you just put it down
and I'll get it after?

22:43.946 --> 22:45.323
- Can I shower?
- [laughs softly]

22:47.450 --> 22:49.619
[Belly] I've always
liked you with wet hair.

22:50.661 --> 22:54.582
It's so... romantic.
[laughs softly]

22:54.582 --> 22:58.086
What's so romantic
about wet hair?

23:01.130 --> 23:02.548
[exhales]

23:02.548 --> 23:04.592
You just don't get it.

23:04.592 --> 23:05.843
[scoffs]

23:07.220 --> 23:08.638
How many of those have you had?

23:11.349 --> 23:13.518
Two, five. It's...

23:13.518 --> 23:14.936
- [chuckles]
- It's not important.

23:16.312 --> 23:18.981
Let me just ask you
one thing, okay?

23:21.609 --> 23:24.487
Did you buy me that infinity
necklace for my birthday?

23:30.493 --> 23:32.495
[laughs]

23:32.495 --> 23:33.871
I knew it.

23:33.871 --> 23:35.081
- I knew I was right.
- Can I please...

23:35.081 --> 23:37.208
Can you give me
some privacy, please?

23:38.584 --> 23:41.546
[Belly] I knew it. I knew it.

23:45.174 --> 23:48.219
[scoffs] Who said
you could have a margarita?

23:48.219 --> 23:51.347
Um, Victoria?

23:51.347 --> 23:53.266
[door closes]

23:53.266 --> 23:56.227
Cake time. [giggles]

23:56.227 --> 23:57.436
[laughs softly]

23:59.772 --> 24:01.649
What? It's cake time.

24:03.526 --> 24:05.528
- [exhales]
- [laughs]

24:07.947 --> 24:09.157
Where'd all the kids go?

24:09.157 --> 24:10.658
Uh, more for us.

24:10.658 --> 24:13.077
That's the spirit, John,
my eternal optimist.

24:13.077 --> 24:15.037
Ooh, I want the piece
with the strawberries!

24:17.206 --> 24:19.083
- Belly, are you okay?
- [Adam] Honey, are you okay?
- [Belly] Ow.

24:19.083 --> 24:20.459
- Here, let me help you up.
- [Susannah] Adam, I'm fine.

24:20.459 --> 24:22.170
- Come on. Please.
- I got it. I got it, stop it.

24:25.339 --> 24:28.134
God, just go away.

24:28.134 --> 24:30.219
[grunts softly]

24:30.219 --> 24:32.013
I-I'm sorry.

24:38.477 --> 24:40.313
[Susannah grunts]

24:42.440 --> 24:45.318
- Mom?
- I'll deal with you later.

24:45.318 --> 24:47.945
Let's ...check on Belly.

24:50.781 --> 24:52.909
Come on. Let's go.

24:54.744 --> 24:56.954
- Dad?
- Yeah, sweetie?

24:56.954 --> 24:59.707
- There you go.
- I think Victoria's
really cool.

24:59.707 --> 25:01.209
That's great, sweetie.

25:12.303 --> 25:14.972
I'm sorry about your
grandmother's cake stand.

25:16.015 --> 25:17.558
Whatever.

25:22.647 --> 25:25.358
Well, I see you're not
wearing your ring.

25:25.358 --> 25:27.652
Want to tell me what the hell
is going on with you and Adam?

25:30.863 --> 25:33.032
I'm sorry, but how
was I supposed to know

25:33.032 --> 25:34.075
the two of you
weren't getting along?

25:34.075 --> 25:35.409
We should get back to the party.

25:35.409 --> 25:36.410
No, we're not leaving this room

25:36.410 --> 25:37.495
until you tell me
what's going on.

25:37.495 --> 25:39.455
[sighs]

25:39.455 --> 25:42.667
He cheated on me three years
ago with his secretary.

25:42.667 --> 25:43.709
What?

25:43.709 --> 25:45.544
While I was going through chemo.

25:45.544 --> 25:46.671
Are you...

25:46.671 --> 25:49.090
- [exhales]
- So '80s, right?

25:49.090 --> 25:52.301
Then again,
Adam never was very creative.

25:52.301 --> 25:54.387
Wait.

25:54.387 --> 25:56.097
Why didn't you tell me?

25:56.097 --> 25:57.848
Because you would've
told me to leave him

25:57.848 --> 26:00.309
and I didn't want to
and now I do.

26:00.309 --> 26:01.769
Why now?

26:01.769 --> 26:04.897
I don't want him
next to me at the end.

26:06.649 --> 26:09.527
